The paper deals with cyber attacks on discrete event systems, which are typically studied in the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The focus is on the manipulation of sensor readings, which is a common technique in cyber attacks (cs.CR). The paper proposes an automaton-based approach to model and analyze the attacks, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed attack strategy, which can be evaluated using machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
